explanation: This solution uses two pointers, i and j, to iterate through the name and typed strings respectively. It checks if the current character in the typed string matches the current character in the name string, and if not, it checks if the current character in the typed string is the same as the previous one. If it's not, it returns false. If it iterates through the entire typed string and the i pointer reaches the end of the name string, it returns true.

